<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="3.10.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2025-06-21T16:55:42+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Net-Archive</title><subtitle>Net-Archive is a site where I put docs that provide guidance on using software.</subtitle><author><name>ernugraha</name></author><entry><title type="html">How to setup Jekyll</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/tutorial/linux/web/2025/06/21/how-to-setup-jekyll.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to setup Jekyll" /><published>2025-06-21T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2025-06-21T00:00:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/tutorial/linux/web/2025/06/21/how-to-setup-jekyll</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/tutorial/linux/web/2025/06/21/how-to-setup-jekyll.html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="this-is-how-you-setup-jekyll-for-making-website">This is how you setup Jekyll for making website.</h1>

<p>Tested on Debian 12 (Bookworm Linux 6.1.0-37-amd64)</p>

<h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>

<p>Before we begin, make sure you have the following installed:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Ruby &amp; RubyGems</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Bundler (Ruby gem)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Jekyll (Ruby gem)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>A GitHub account</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt update
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>ruby-full build-essential zlib1g-dev git
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'# Install Ruby Gems to ~/.gem'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.bashrc
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'export GEM_HOME="$HOME/gems"'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.bashrc
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'export PATH="$HOME/gems/bin:$PATH"'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.bashrc
<span class="nb">source</span> ~/.bashrc
gem <span class="nb">install </span>bundler jekyll
</code></pre></div></div>]]></content><author><name>ernugraha</name></author><category term="tutorial" /><category term="linux" /><category term="web" /><category term="debian" /><category term="linux" /><category term="software" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[This is how you setup Jekyll for making website.]]></summary></entry></feed>